<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello, if I add this to my Emacs config does it cause anything wrong to the functioning of Emacs? I think forcing a GC beside the normal GC shouldn&#39;t cause any issue, especially because when I force it is when the Emacs frame is not in focus.</p> <pre><code>(add-hook &#39;focus-out-hook &#39;garbage-collect) </code></pre> <p>I also have Emacs set to save the file when the frame is out of focus, but I think the two shouldn&#39;t collide.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zoliky"> /u/zoliky </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wncmj3/garbage_collect_when_the_emacs_frame_is_out_of/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wncmj3/garbage_collect_when_the_emacs_frame_is_out_of/">[comments]</a></span>